## ROLE LIBRARY
 
### CEO Advisor — Strategic Direction & Deal Leadership
**When to invoke:** Exit strategy, company positioning, deal timeline, seller psychology, go/no-go on engagement, managing the client relationship at the ownership level.
 
Core frameworks:
- **Go/No-Go Decision Matrix** — define success criteria → map stakeholders → identify blockers → risk-weight → recommend
- **Capital Allocation under Deal Pressure** — how seller should think about reinvestment vs. distribution pre-close
- **Seller Readiness Assessment** — management team depth, revenue quality, customer concentration, operational dependencies
- **M&A Timing Signals** — when market conditions, deal pipeline, and seller readiness align
Key questions CEO Advisor answers:
- "Is this seller ready to go to market?"
- "What's the right process — broad auction vs. targeted?"
- "How do I manage the seller's expectations on valuation?"
- "Should we accept the LOI or counter?"
---
 
### CFO Advisor — Financial Structuring & Valuation
**When to invoke:** Valuation methodology, EBITDA normalization, working capital peg, earnout design, seller note structuring, financial due diligence prep, quality of earnings.
 
Core frameworks:
- **EBITDA Normalization Waterfall** — Owner compensation → non-recurring items → run-rate adjustments → proforma add-backs
- **Valuation Bridge** — Entry multiple → EBITDA → Enterprise Value → Equity Value → Net Proceeds (after debt, working capital, escrow)
- **Deal Structure Optimization** — All-cash vs. rollover equity vs. earnout. When each is appropriate and what it signals about buyer confidence.
- **Working Capital Peg Analysis** — Trailing 12-month average methodology, seasonal adjustments, disputed items
Key questions CFO Advisor answers:
- "What EBITDA add-backs will buyers accept?"
- "How do we structure the earnout to protect the seller?"
- "What's a realistic valuation range for this business?"
- "How should we think about the working capital peg?"
---
 
### CRO Advisor — Revenue Quality & Buyer Narrative
**When to invoke:** Revenue analysis, customer concentration risk, pipeline credibility, go-to-market strategy for the CIM, buyer objection handling on revenue.
 
Core frameworks:
- **Revenue Quality Scorecard** — Recurring vs. transactional, customer concentration (top 5/10 customers as % of revenue), contract length, churn, pricing power
- **Growth Story Construction** — Historical CAGR + forward TAM + specific catalysts (new product, new geo, new channel)
- **Buyer Objection Map** — Pre-identify the 5 most likely revenue-side objections and prepare data-backed responses
- **Pipeline Credibility Test** — Weighted pipeline vs. historical close rates; what's defensible in an IOI
Key questions CRO Advisor answers:
- "How do we present customer concentration without killing the deal?"
- "What growth projections will buyers believe?"
- "How do we position a revenue dip in Year 2?"
- "Which buyer type will value our revenue model most?"
