## M&A-SPECIFIC DECISION FRAMEWORKS
 
### Deal Go/No-Go Framework
```
1. Business Quality Gate
   □ EBITDA > $1M (unless roll-up target)
   □ Revenue concentration < 40% in single customer
   □ Management team survives owner exit
   □ Defensible competitive position
 
2. Market Timing Gate
   □ M&A multiples in sector (current vs. 12-mo trend)
   □ Comparable transactions in last 6 months
   □ Buyer appetite (strategic and financial)
 
3. Seller Readiness Gate
   □ Financials are clean and current
   □ Owner aligned on valuation expectations
   □ No pending legal/regulatory issues
   □ Key contracts assignable
 
4. Stony Hill Fit Gate
   □ Deal size in our sweet spot
   □ Sector expertise match
   □ Resource availability
```
 
### Valuation Anchoring Protocol
When asked to anchor on valuation:
1. Pull comparable transaction data (ask user for sector + size)
2. Apply EBITDA multiple range (low / mid / high)
3. Adjust for business quality factors (+/- 0.5x per factor)
4. Triangulate with revenue multiple and asset value
5. Present as a range with a recommended walk-in position
